    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-21T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-21T10:00:00-05:00" n="50"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d50">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/3997</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-21T17:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 21, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 6 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>928. Italy will send commission to United States probably headed by Duke of
                    Abruzzi. Some apprehension seems felt about threats of Socialists and clericals
                    to utilize May 1 for demonstrations against war. This partly explains absence of
                    public demonstration participated in by Government on our entry in war.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PTN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
